  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "To quickly unfollow people on Instagram, you have several options:\n\n1. **Manual Unfollow**:\n   - Open the Instagram app and go to your profile by tapping your profile picture in the bottom right corner.\n   - Tap 'Following' to see the list of people you\u2019re already following.\n   - Scroll through the list and find the user you want to unfollow.\n   - Tap the \u201cFollowing\u201d button next to their name to unfollow them.\n   - Confirm if prompted.\n\n2. **Using the 'Following' Tab**:\n   - Open the Instagram app and go to your profile.\n   - Tap on the 'Following' tab.\n   - In this list, you can see all the users you follow. You can quickly tap the \"Following\" button next to each user to unfollow them.\n\n3. **Using Third-Party Apps**:\n   - There are several third-party applications available that can help you manage your Instagram account, including unfollowing users in bulk. Some popular apps include 'Cleaner for IG', 'Followers Chief', and similar apps.\n\n**Note**: Be cautious when using third-party apps and ensure they are reputable to avoid compromising your account security.\n\n4. **On a Web Browser**:\n   - Go to instagram.com and log into your account.\n   - Click on your profile picture to go to your profile.\n   - Click on \"Following\" to see the list.\n   - Unfollow users by clicking the \"Following\" button next to their names and confirming.\n\n5. **Using the 'Least Interacted With' Option**:\n   - Open Instagram and go to your profile.\n   - Tap 'Following' and then select 'Least interacted with'.\n   - This will show you a list of accounts you have interacted with the least over the last 90 days. You can unfollow from this list to quickly curate your following list.\n\nBy using these methods, you can be more efficient in managing the people you follow on Instagram.",
